# NPE ShiftBot - Alternative Deployment Options (No Restrictions)

## üöÄ Free Hosting Platforms (No Restrictions)

### 1. GitHub Pages (Recommended)
**Best for:** Static sites, version control integration
**Cost:** Free
**Features:** Custom domains, HTTPS, unlimited bandwidth

#### Setup Steps:
1. Push your code to GitHub repository
2. Go to Repository Settings ‚Üí Pages
3. Select source branch (main/master)
4. Your site will be available at: `https://username.github.io/repository-name`

#### Custom Domain Setup:
```bash
# Add CNAME file with your domain
echo "your-domain.com" > CNAME
git add CNAME
git commit -m "Add custom domain"
git push
```

### 2. Netlify
**Best for:** Modern web apps, continuous deployment
**Cost:** Free tier with 100GB bandwidth
**Features:** Form handling, serverless functions, edge computing

#### Deployment Methods:
- **Git Integration:** Connect your GitHub repo for auto-deployment
- **Drag & Drop:** Upload your HTML file directly
- **CLI Deployment:**
```bash
npm install -g netlify-cli
netlify deploy --prod --dir .
```

### 3. Vercel
**Best for:** React, Next.js, but supports static HTML
**Cost:** Free for personal projects
**Features:** Global CDN, instant deployments, analytics

#### Quick Deploy:
```bash
npm install -g vercel
vercel --prod
```

### 4. Firebase Hosting
**Best for:** Google ecosystem integration
**Cost:** Free tier with 10GB storage
**Features:** Global CDN, SSL certificates, custom domains

#### Setup:
```bash
npm install -g firebase-tools
firebase login
firebase init hosting
firebase deploy
```

### 5. Surge.sh
**Best for:** Quick static deployments
**Cost:** Free for custom domains
**Features:** Simple CLI deployment, instant publishing

#### Deploy:
```bash
npm install -g surge
surge
```

## üñ•Ô∏è Self-Hosting Options

### 1. DigitalOcean Droplets
**Cost:** $5/month
**Features:** Full server control, root access, scalable

#### Quick Setup:
```bash
# Create Ubuntu droplet
# Install Nginx
sudo apt update
sudo apt install nginx
sudo systemctl start nginx

# Upload your files
scp -r * user@your-server-ip:/var/www/html/
```

### 2. AWS S3 + CloudFront
**Cost:** Pay-as-you-go (very cheap for static sites)
**Features:** Global CDN, 99.99% uptime, enterprise-grade

#### Setup Script:
```bash
# Install AWS CLI
pip install awscli
aws configure

# Create S3 bucket
aws s3 mb s3://npe-shiftbot
aws s3 sync . s3://npe-shiftbot --delete
aws s3 website s3://npe-shiftbot --index-document index.html
```

### 3. Cloudflare Pages
**Cost:** Free
**Features:** Global CDN, unlimited bandwidth, analytics

#### Deploy:
1. Connect GitHub repository
2. Set build command: `echo "Static site"`
3. Set publish directory: `/`
4. Deploy automatically

